Sorry for the prolonged review.
Now this is what I am seeing:
http://ci.tensorflow.org/job/tensorflow-pr-win-cmake-pytest/1/

The script I execute is this:

call "C:\program files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 14.0\VC\vcvarsall.bat"
cd tensorflow/contrib/cmake
rmdir build /S /Q
mkdir build
cd build
"C:\program files\cmake\bin\cmake.exe" .. -A x64 -DSWIG_EXECUTABLE=C:\ProgramData\chocolatey\bin\swig.exe -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\python.exe" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DPYTHON_LIBRARIES="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\libs\python35.lib" -Dtensorflow_BUILD_PYTHON_TESTS=ON
"C:\Program Files (x86)\MSBuild\14.0\Bin\msbuild" /p:Configuration=Release /maxcpucount:32 tf_python_build_pip_package.vcxproj
ctest -C Release -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\python.exe"

All tests seem to be failing, any idea what is wrong?
Also no logs are visible. Can we modify the tf tests cmake file to print out the test log in case of test failure?

body:
Sorry for the prolonged review.
Now this is what I am seeing:
http://ci.tensorflow.org/job/tensorflow-pr-win-cmake-pytest/1/

The script I execute is this:

```
call "C:\program files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio 14.0\VC\vcvarsall.bat"
cd tensorflow/contrib/cmake
rmdir build /S /Q
mkdir build
cd build
"C:\program files\cmake\bin\cmake.exe" .. -A x64 -DSWIG_EXECUTABLE=C:\ProgramData\chocolatey\bin\swig.exe -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\python.exe" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DPYTHON_LIBRARIES="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\libs\python35.lib" -Dtensorflow_BUILD_PYTHON_TESTS=ON
"C:\Program Files (x86)\MSBuild\14.0\Bin\msbuild" /p:Configuration=Release /maxcpucount:32 tf_python_build_pip_package.vcxproj
ctest -C Release -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE="C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\python.exe"
```

All tests seem to be failing, any idea what is wrong?
Also no logs are visible. Can we modify the tf tests cmake file to print out the test log in case of test failure?
